Defines the way that IO-Link events are mapped to PROFINET diagnostics.
According to IO-Link Integration to PROFINET Edition 1: Well known IO-Link events will be mapped to the corresponding PROFINET diagnostics.
Murrelektronik IO-Link extended integration: Mapping of IO-Link events to PROFINET diagnostics will be done according to Murrelektronik IO-Link integration. Vendor specific events for Murrelektronik devices will get clear text messages. Extended events with channel information will be used for Murrelektronik devices supporting this feature.

Defines, if process alarms are generated on receipt of a notification from the IO-Link device.
Discard: Notifications from the IO-Link device will just be discarded.
Create process alarm: A process alarm will be created for every notification from the IO-Link device.
Defines the mode of the IO-Link port.
Defines the rate, at which process data should be exchanged between IO-Link master and the IO-Link device.

Defines, if checks are done for the right device and the handling of data storage.
No device check: No checks for compatibility of the device are done. Data storage stored in the master is erased. Data storage will not be used.
Compatible device (V1.0): The connected device is checked for compatibility with the given vendor ID and device ID. Data storage stored in the master is erased. Data storage will not be used.
Compatible device (V1.1): The connected device is checked for compatibility with the given vendor ID and device ID. Data storage stored in the master is erased. Data storage will not be used.
Compatible device with backup and restore (V1.1): The connected device is checked for compatibility with the given vendor ID and device ID. Parameterization is backed up from the device to the master and restored from the master back to the device.
Compatible device with restore (V1.1): The connected device is checked for compatibility with the given vendor ID and device ID. Parameterization is only restored from the master back to the device.

Defines, if checks are done for the right device and the handling of data storage.
No device check: No checks for compatibility of the device are done. Data storage stored in the master is erased. Data storage will not be used.
Compatible device (V1.0): The connected device is checked for compatibility with the given vendor ID and device ID. Data storage stored in the master is erased. Data storage will not be used.
Compatible device (V1.1): The connected device is checked for compatibility with the given vendor ID and device ID. Data storage stored in the master is erased. Data storage will not be used.
Compatible device with backup and restore (V1.1): The connected device is checked for compatibility with the given vendor ID and device ID. Parameterization is backed up from the device to the master and restored from the master back to the device.
Compatible device with restore (V1.1): The connected device is checked for compatibility with the given vendor ID and device ID. Parameterization is only restored from the master back to the device.
